description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Resident Medical Officer to join our team at Cygnet.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play a crucial role within our services providing on call cover for Cygnet Hospital Harrogate. Cygnet Hospital Harrogate is a long-established mental health hospital that provides an emergency admissions service across two acute wards.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The RMO is the doctor onsite at all times, covering on call between 5pm and 9am and weekend shifts. Generally you will work on a fortnightly rota of 4 days on / 3 days off and then 3 days on / 4 days off.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; All sites have accommodation and meals provided.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;The duties that RMOs are expected to carry out are as follows:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ECGs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bloods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NG tubing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patient admissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patient assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Risk assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mental Health Assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full GMC registration and an MBBS (or equivalent) medical qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Psychiatry is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to demonstrate sound clinical judgment / experience in making clinical decision and managing risk and knows when to seek help&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal / written communication skills along with the ability to interview, assess and treat patients and write clear comprehensive medical notes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven record of CPD (Continued Professional Development)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary up to £60,000 (Depending on Experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical indemnity cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPD support and study leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active participation in clinical governance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous annual leave entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributory pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Health Care was established in 1988. Since then we have developed a wide range of services for individuals with mental health needs and learning disabilities within the UK. We have built a reputation for delivering pioneering services and outstanding outcomes for the people in our care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: successful candidates will be required to undergo an enhanced DBS check.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Are you seeking a new and rewarding challenge where you can make a positive change?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Click the link to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
